§I role
  W! action-RPG W! seamless-input-fluidity ← KB+M ↔ controller ↔ touch
  ¬ force-rebind-on-mode-switch ; LAST-source-wins · 500ms-grace
  W! accessibility-first ← remappable EVERY action · OS-integration
  W! sovereign-cap-aim-assist ← anti-bullying-axiom · ¬ pay-to-aim-better
  ¬ ALL : input_genre_fluid ⊆ catalog-only-Rust ⊑ no-runtime-deps

§I input-modes (4 mutually-exclusive)
  W! 1.KeyboardMouse        · WASD + mouse-aim · default-PC
  W! 2.GamepadXinput        · standard-Xbox · LeftStick + RightStick + auto-aim-assist (toggleable)
  W! 3.GamepadDualSense     · PS5 · adaptive-trigger-aware · haptic-feedback channel
  W! 4.TouchScreen          · mobile/tablet · virtual-stick + tap-to-act · UI-prompts shift

§I auto-detection
  W! source-tag per-event ← {Keyboard, Mouse, GamepadXinput, GamepadDualSense, Touch}
  W! last-input-source becomes-active · grace-window = 500ms
  W! grace-prevents-thrashing ← rapid-source-switch held until silent-period elapses
  W! UI-prompt-strings shift atomically when active-mode changes
    KB+M  : "press F to interact" · "WASD to move"
    Pad   : "press X to interact" · "left-stick to move"
    Touch : "tap to interact"     · "drag-stick to move"
  ✓ deterministic ← timestamp-driven · replay-bit-equal across input-source change

§I per-mode bindings (genre-fluid · matches camera-mode W13-4)
  W! Fps-mode + KB+M
    · move = WASD · aim = mouse-delta · jump = Space · crouch = LCtrl · sprint = LShift
    · interact = F · ADS = RMB-hold · fire = LMB · reload = R
  W! Fps-mode + Gamepad
    · move = LeftStick · aim = RightStick + auto-aim-assist (toggleable · sovereign-cap)
    · jump = A/Cross · crouch = B/Circle · sprint = LeftStickClick
    · interact = X/Square · ADS = LT/L2-hold · fire = RT/R2 · reload = Y/Triangle
  W! ThirdPerson-mode + KB+M
    · move = WASD · cam = mouse-orbit · sprint = LShift
  W! Isometric-mode + KB+M
    · move = click-to-move + edge-scroll · aim = mouse-cursor
  W! TopDown-mode + Gamepad
    · move = LeftStick · cursor = RightStick · fire-direction = RightStick

§I accessibility (5+ features · OS-integration)
  W! remappable EVERY action
    · per-action-binding-table · save/load JSON ← cap-anonymous-share-allowed
    · ¬ require account ← local-config first-class
  W! hold-to-toggle per-action
    · crouch-toggle · ADS-toggle · sprint-toggle ← per-action-config (independent)
  W! OS-integration sticky/slow/bounce keys
    · sticky-keys ← single-key-press = modifier-stays-down (Win/Mac/Linux supported)
    · slow-keys   ← min-press-duration before key-registers
    · bounce-keys ← debounce repeat-fires within window
  W! mouse-acceleration toggle · DPI-tunable
    · raw-input-mode (no-OS-accel) · DPI 100..6400
  W! visual-input-prompts ← localizable string-keys ← ¬ hardcoded (WCAG)
  W! haptic-channel (DualSense + Switch + future)
    · cap-rumble-strength 0..1 · per-event-class

§I aim-assist (5-tier · sovereign-cap · anti-bullying-axiom)
  W! tier 0 = OFF      · zero-magnetism · zero-friction · default
  W! tier 1 = LIGHT    · 0.10 magnetism · 0.05 friction · subtle ← accessibility-default
  W! tier 2 = MODERATE · 0.20 magnetism · 0.10 friction · controller-default
  W! tier 3 = STRONG   · 0.35 magnetism · 0.20 friction · low-vision-cap
  W! tier 4 = MAX      · 0.50 magnetism · 0.30 friction · sovereign-only-grant
  W! sovereign-cap-flow
    · mode-3+ requires SovereignAttest ← cap-table-entry "input.aim_assist.high"
    · mode-4 requires explicit consent-prompt + reason-reason-tag
    · ¬ pay-tier ← cosmetic-only-axiom ; ALL tiers freely-available to caps-granted players
    · anti-bullying : in PvP-context, server clamps tier ≤ player-class-cap (no pay-to-win)
  ✓ deterministic ← magnetism applied to aim-vector pre-physics · replay-bit-equal

§I integration-points
  W! consume RawEvent from input.rs (W11-1 · existing TextInputState preserved)
  W! emit ActiveInputMode → ui_overlay (UI-prompt-shift)
  W! emit AimAssistVector → camera + weapon (additive to RawAim · pre-recoil)
  W! emit BindingMap → settings + cssl-host-config (persist + share)
  W! consume CameraMode from genre_fluid_camera.rs (W13-4 · per-mode-binding-set)
  ¬ touch input.rs internals · TextInputState · VirtualKey enum
  ¬ touch render · network · physics

